{"word":"λισσάς","slug":"λισσάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λισσάς</b></el> <el>(λισσάς, άδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:peculiar'>pecul.</a> <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:λισσός'><el>λισσός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>smooth, bare</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a bare, smooth cliff</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}